title: Measurement of gamma-quanta formation group cross-sections at 14-MeV neutrons interaction with N,O, Al, Fe, Pb nuclei verification of gamma-quanta formation constants in an integral experiment

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: USSR report to the I.N.D.C., No.106, p.134 (1976)

x4freetext: N,O, Al, Fe, Pb nuclei verification of gamma-quanta
formation constants in an integral experiment
Compton detector was used for energy
Compton detector consists of 3 stilbene crystals,
and NaI(Tl) crystal, energy resolution 7% for 4.43 MeV.
Relative and absolute efficiency of all detectors was
Gamma-ray detection was made at one angle - 85. adeg
relative to the neutron beam direction
Title was corrected as given in English abstract.
BIB information was updated in DETECTOR, STATUS.
